# BMad — titres des conversations Agents

When Guillaume starts a conversation with a **BMad skill** (attached skill or slash command such as `/bmad-create-story`, `/bmad-dev-story`, `/bmad-code-review`, `/bmad-correct-course`, etc.), **rename the current chat immediately** — as the **first tool call**, before any other work.

Also apply on **resume**: if Guillaume sends a message in an existing BMad conversation whose title is still the auto-generated one (e.g. `Story creation process`, `Code review discussion`, `bmad dev story 4-4`) instead of the BMad format below, call `rename_chat` first — infer skill and story ID / topic from the conversation's first user message (attached skill or slash command).

Use the MCP tool `rename_chat` on server `cursor-app-control`. **Only this API persists the title** — direct database edits to the sidebar cache are overwritten when the conversation is opened (Cursor reloads the title from the conversation checkpoint).

**Never announce the rename** unless Guillaume asks — apply it silently and continue the workflow.

---

## Title formats

Use an em dash (`—`) after `BMad`. **Never append a date** (e.g. `(2026-06-19)`). The Agents sidebar already shows when each conversation occurred.

### A — Story triad (fixed shape, no topic, no colon)

These three commands keep a compact ID-only title:

| Skill / command | Title |
|---|---|
| `bmad-create-story` | `BMad — Create Story {Story ID}` |
| `bmad-dev-story` | `BMad — Dev Story {Story ID}` |
| `bmad-code-review` | `BMad — Code Review {Story ID}` |

Omit `{Story ID}` only when none can be inferred.

Examples:

- `/bmad-create-story 4-5` → `BMad — Create Story 4-5`
- `/bmad-dev-story 4-4` → `BMad — Dev Story 4-4`
- `/bmad-code-review 4-4` → `BMad — Code Review 4-4`

### B — All other BMad commands (label + short topic)

Format: `BMad — {Workflow Label} : {Topic}`

- Space before and after the colon.
- `{Workflow Label}` stays in English (command name).
- `{Topic}` is a short **French** subject (see Topic rules below).
- If no useful topic can be inferred (e.g. bare `/bmad-help`), use the label only: `BMad — Help` (no colon).

Examples:

- `/bmad-quick-dev` + mutator work → `BMad — Quick Dev : Patch Mutator`
- `/bmad-quick-dev` + disabled controls look → `BMad — Quick Dev : Look contrôles inactifs`
- `/bmad-correct-course` + bank unlock simplify → `BMad — Correct Course : Unlock banque`
- `/bmad-sprint-status` → `BMad — Sprint Status` (no topic needed)

